1 Introduction
**************

Pimacs is an Emacs client for Pi Coding Agent (https://pi.dev/).  It
provides an interactive interface to the Pi Coding Agent directly from
Emacs.


File: pimacs.info,  Node: Setup,  Next: Usage,  Prev: Introduction,  Up: Top

2 Setup
*******

2.1 Install the Pimacs Agent
============================

First, install the Pimacs agent using npm:

     npm install -g --ignore-scripts @earendil-works/pi-coding-agent

   Then start Pimacs and run ‘/login’ to configure your provider:

     pi

2.2 Install ‘pimacs.el’
=======================

Add the following to your Emacs configuration:

     (use-package pimacs
       :ensure t
       :vc (:url "git@github.com:ananthakumaran/pimacs.el.git"
            :rev :newest)
       :commands (pimacs-chat))


File: pimacs.info,  Node: Usage,  Next: Sandbox,  Prev: Setup,  Up: Top

3 Usage
*******

Run ‘M-x pimacs-chat’ from any file in your project to start a Pimacs
chat session.  Use a prefix argument (‘C-u M-x pimacs-chat’) to start
multiple chats on the same project.

   The chat buffer is read-only except for the prompt input area.  Use
‘RET’ to submit a prompt and ‘C-j’ to insert a newline.  Press ‘i’ from
anywhere in the chat buffer to move point to the prompt input area.

