4 Sandbox
*********

To run Pimacs inside a sandbox, customize ‘pimacs-executable’ and
‘pimacs-flags’:

     (setq pimacs-executable "nono")
     (setq pimacs-flags '("run" "--silent" "--profile" "pi" "--allow-cwd" "--" "pi"
                      "--tools" "read,bash,edit,write,grep,find,ls"))


File: pimacs.info,  Node: How It Works,  Next: Keybindings,  Prev: Sandbox,  Up: Top

5 How It Works
**************

Emacs starts Pimacs in RPC mode (https://pi.dev/docs/latest/rpc).  In
this setup, Pimacs handles the agent logic while Emacs provides the user
interface.  Some features, such as ‘/login’ and ‘/logout’, are not
supported (https://github.com/earendil-works/pi/issues/885) because they
are not currently exposed through the RPC API.


